Still in disbelief. @theeddieaikau most close outs sets I’ve ever seen at the bay in my life.The OGs said they couldn’t  recall another day they could really compare it to.. caught this wave from the middle of the bay paddling back out after a previous wave. It closed out the whole bay and was  pushing me way to fast towards the jump rock..luckily made it far enough near shore to where the current was switching & pulling back to the other end of the bay. Wana send a huge thank you to @hawaiianwaterpatrol and the North Shore Life Guards for working hard all day to keep us safe as can on a day like that. My last heat I got one of the top 5 beatings of my life…last minutes of my last  heat so I decided I’m  just gonna send it on a wave no matter what, well that didn’t happen 😂 missed the wave I was paddling for then seen black walls coming towards me,Out the back in the vortex of the craziest mountains of ocean breaking right on my head, very close to 2 wave hold down & thrashing me so violently, barely getting a good breath before the next waves began blasting me across & in back towards the jump rock, where the SandBar underwater current chaos was outta control. After around  10-12 continuous waves on my head I was really about to pass out from exhaustion&lack of oxygen, I was aware of it, stayed as calm as possible but luckily brada @nolandkeaulana came in Clutch right before things coulda got a lot more complicated. I was able to get my leash off, my arm up and he flew me on that sled like it was nothing 💪he told me once we hit the beach that he seen my face starting to look blue so he knew he had to come risk it to get me, those guys are warriors and guardian angels.my big wave sessions never feel complete unless I catch cracks on one at least, so it was a good day in my book🙌 also Mahalo @jamie.sterling letting me borrow your leash it did it’s job good :) 📷: @yoshitanaka1

Mahalo to Dr.Schifflet and the whole team at @discmd for taking such good care of me yesterday! Back surgery was a success, instant relief from the herniation pressing on my S1 nerve constantly, now just some general pain from incision area but nothing compared to the type of pain was dealing with for 6-8 months now. They performed a L5 Lumbar Discectomy, can swipe left to see the herniated material from my disc that was causing the compression on my nerve, to read Dr.Shiflett validify the amount of pain , after all the surgery’s he has performed on all different type of extreme athletes and everyday injuries, it  felt good knowing I haven’t been being a lil wimp about my pain 😂I was in at 1pm and discharged at 9:30pm, now I gotta spend my time with extra conscious TLC to let the tear from the herniation heal up over next few months and onwards. Rest/Recovery , diet, suplements, oxygenation:circulation , BLT (bending,lifting,twisting:turning) are first up on the list of things i will be conquering, not supposed  to lift anything over 10lbs for about 6 weeks,  after about a month the Physical therapy will be put in to play, consistency and positivity are gonna be key for me for 100% successful Post-Op Praying  to be surfing and living at full speed within 4-8 months. Mahalo for all the Love and Support🤙 & Mahalo Ke Akua  for all the blessings 🙏❤️PS- thank you to all of the doctors,healers, family and friends for the positivity and help along the way , thank you @darianwailani for flying out with our son to support me every step of the way as you always have, thank you @pmtenore for posting me up at your house and taking care of me, and thank you dad and mom @liam__mcnamara @seamaids_brandeemcnamara for everything. There is countless others to name specifically and just know your not being forgotten I’m just done editing this post and going back to sleep 😂❤️ LOVE&am GRATEFUL for all of you !

Went to Sunset beach elementary school across the street from Pipe, when the medivac helicopters use to land in the field to rush people to the hospital (my dad @liam__mcnamara was one of those last heli rides after breaking his Femur) ..first time I saw a lifeless body was after school walking down to see what pipeline was doing..I’ve witnessed strangers, friends, family and legends get seriously injured, occasionally perishing, from this magical place …it really is no joke and the moment you get comfortable you’ll get put right back in your place & humbled…this wave has fascinated me since a little kid, she seems to have mystical powers that pulls the brave hearted in to her allure and never lets em go..I love pipeline and don’t see myself ever not participating in the calculated chaos of dancing with her until I physically can’t… being inside of her, riding just right and being embodied in her release, sex nor drugs can compare ❤️She has all true Pipeline warriors by the balls #pipeline #northshore #warrior #love

Think this was around 2015,I had been practicing guitar/singing/songwriting very disciplined like(although wasn’t discipline for me because I was infatuated with it and my idols like JimiHendrix&Bob Marley to name a couple,  filled the walls In the dungeon downstairs of my house where I’d spend most of my time trying to emulate them skill). I had done a handful of guitar lessons at a younger age but it never stuck because it felt like more school after school trying to learn music theory and my ADHD just wanted to play…it’s always been about feeling for me for surfing and for music…(only recently I cared to know dimensions of my surf boards, I’d just feel em in hands and know if it was for me or not haha) Fast forward a few years the time I really caught the bug I had a friend named Toa who was a good guitar player and singer, who would come out from town and sleep at our house…he began teaching me songs we where actually listening to on a daily basis.. started out teaching me bar chords( not east for beginner fingers), i remember specifically beginning to learn  how to play “True Love” and a few other @sojagram songs and I was always amazed when he’d play @slightlystoopid “closer to the sun” acoustic and eventually he began to teach  me that. Afterwards it was alot of YouTube tutorials ( Honestly a great place to learn basically anything ) and by jamming with anyone who wanted to jam. This pic was from a trip my uncle @dlkjet flew me out to SantaMonica to help me progress my songwriting and try to record some stuff, I never ending up releasing anything from that trip but it was a awsome learning experience meeting successful people in the music industry and being out on my own staying in Venice beach at 16-17years old. I’m working on revisiting that passion and feel myself reconnecting with it, ironically as my hair happens to be the same length as this pic for the first time since then 😂 I’ve gone through phases when I wouldn’t pick up an instrument for months on end and hated music, or would try to make music for the wrong reasons..It’s been a wild ride and I’m really lucky to even be alive.. I’m so happy to be lovingMusic&LIFE again

This was my first wave at the @theeddieaikau Before paddling out I  went up in scaffolding to get a better view over the white wash in foreground,needed to confirm what had seemed like underground 30ft waves ..I could see it ledging super hard In a spot of Waimea bay that usually doesn’t break, made the choice to use my 9’9 instead of 11’6.. my plan for sitting way out the back and rolling in to the biggest one I could find went right out the window as that big of board wouldn’t fit in the face of these beasts & at that time of day there wasn’t any Chip-Shots yet…im very confident with bigger boards…at a young age my dad instilled in me that if you can fit a big board in to a small fast steep drop and ride the barrel you’ll be better acclimated  to do it foreal in bigger serious conditions… the waves that morning had a nasty boil  gurgling&bubbling up from the depths lining up with right where you had to ride through… the saying you never know till you go?  in a situation where the clocks ticking…you’ve been waiting for this moment the majority if your  life..time to find out! best way I knew to handle it was  taking deep breaths relaxing enough to not blow 1 of my 4 waves on a bad judgment call, also knowing id better get it goin! so that’s what I did, waited for what seemed like a bomb, and didn’t hesitate. It was a steep drop..I love grabbing my rail on late ones at Waimea but decided it was best to put all of my weight on my tail for this one as you can see from the water displacement by my back foot the entire ride…, I just remember looking down and seeing that boil looking at me like mythical monster of the sea, all of the sudden the bottom 3rd of the wave seems to drop out on me like a giant step…it was subtle, happening very fast, but in slow-mo you can see my body extending & arms flaring compensating for that 10 foot extra drop after my initial drop… ended up riding this one to the Chanel completing the wave and getting a 10point ride. Being back side you don’t see much of the wave just focusing on what’s in your eyesight..no time to blink..felt pretty minor but was pleasantly surprised by pics… was an experience! #waimea #warrior

What’s going on in the world right now is PureEvil.The Hamas acted in pure Evil, Israel government is now acting in pure Evil…  was hesitant to talk about it because I never know what to really believe… Im confident I know enough to know the whole thing is completely fucked up ! the ammount of inoccent children&babies being horrifically Murdered is heart breaking, soul crushing & wrong in every way .. Cause and effect doesn’t matter much to me when the lives of inoccent pure souls without a chance to grow are being wiped off the face of the earth .. a friend shared with me a great analogy , if there’s a robber in a bank holding hostages , do we blow up the whole bank?The Hamas are the robber in this scenario and the hostages are the innocent Palestinian children of Gaza  being blown up by the Israeli government with the support of the United States government ! Sparking flames in me to share my support through song, the world needs Peace…instagram videos of the terror happening been keeping me up late , tonight I wrote some thoughts in to lyrics,more to share soon..
